**[1858, 12-30] Ms.A.1.2.28.166**

Philip Carpenter to WLG; Albany

He has arrived in the U.S. on “slave hunting ground.” “The
{u}appearance{/u} of N. Y. & Albany is somewhat Franco-Germanian; but I
saw one thing {u}essentially{/u} American, on a Bus--- ‘Coloured Persons
{u}allowed{/u} here.’ !!!!” Plans to do some lecturing in Canada.

